<font color="#FF0000">BIRDMEN AND BIRDS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 13 23:29:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I awoke in my bunker one morning..<br>
when all sweet things are born.<br>
A tiny Vietnamese bird perched upon my sill,<br>
to signal the coming morn.<br>
Its voice was loud and clear, <br>
so strongly did it sing<br>
that thoughts of sleep evaporated <br>
and a plan into my heart did spring.<br>
It paused its raucious singing..<br>
It paused for a moment's lull..<br>
I Quickly reached for my helmet<br>
..and crushed his stupid skull!<br><br>
Dedicated to Sparrow Droppings and other bird brains!<br><br>
MTF
